If CS behaves similarly to SES, it will be very interesting for the economy, as we will have two distinct and very specific forms of resource extraction:
1 - Through mining, where the player chooses a specific resource and harvests it abundantly, potentially finding rarer resources in the mining process if they are lucky (and have a perk for this);
2 - Through Claim Stake, where the player who owns the land mines all possible resources on that land, but at a much slower rate than if they were using a mining ship. If they want to intensify the extraction of one or another resource, they must build additional structures on the land, which will consume more resources but will increase the rate of obtaining the desired resource.

@Deleted User Hi, I was evaluating this with my friends and we noticed this gameplay style in the races.

As long as you move in a straight line with the ship forward, your speed limit is approximately 115 +/-. When you move almost sideways, the speed limit increases, sometimes reaching 130.

I wanted to know if this is the goal or if it needs to be revised? We believe it's a bug or something in the formula that, instead of decreasing, adds the two speeds together.
